    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Hey Viola!"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p><b>Hey Viola!</b>, is a musical exploration of Canadian Civil Rights hero, Viola Desmond and could not be more relevant in this time of Civil Rights, Black Lives Matter, and Women's Rights movements. </p>\n\n<p>In <b>Hey Viola!</b>, Vancouver songstress and actor Krystle Dos Santos, with the support of local musicians Chris Davis, Steven Charles and Jen Lewin brings the life of Viola Desmond to the stage using the dynamic and inspirational music that filled the home of this trailblazer of the civil rights movement. Using the musical format enriches the telling of her amazing and powerful story, ultimately an important Canadian story.</p>\n\n<p><b><u>Creative Team</b></u><br>\n\n<b>Krystle Dos Santos:</b>  Co-Creator & Lead Role<br>\n<b>Tracey Power:</b>  Co-Creator & Director  <br>\n<b>Sereana Malani:</b>  Associate Director<br>\n<b>Steve Charles:</b>  Musical Director/Bass/Guitar<br>\n<b>Mary Ancheta:</b>  Piano<br>\n<b>Chris Davis:</b>  Drums/Trumpet<br>\n<b>CS Fergusson-Vaux:</b>  Costume Designer <br>\n<b>Jillian White:</b>  LightingDesigner<br>\n<b>Drew Facey:</b>  Set Designer<br>\n<b>Angela Beaulieu:</b>  Stage Manager</p>\n\n<p><b><a href='https://www.musicaltheatreworks.ca/shows/hey-viola' target='_blank'>musicaltheatreworks.ca/shows/hey-viola</a></b></p>\n\n<iframe width='560' height='315' src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/8KtgE3PTPHo?si=8PiRIzZUTsmfk0Tm' title='YouTube video player' frameborder='0' allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share' referrerpolicy='strict-origin-when-cross-origin' allowfullscreen></iframe>\n\n<style>\n@media screen and (max-width: 600px){iframe{width:100%;}}\n.location-page-temp {display: block!important;}\n</style>"
      }
    ],
