    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Kutumb Kirtan"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Kutumb Kirrtan is a thoughtfully crafted Marathi family drama that reflects the evolving realities of modern households. As the traditional joint family system gradually fades, emotional distances often emerge even among family members living under the same roof. The narrative explores the delicate balance between long held traditions and contemporary aspirations through the life of a young man raised in a conventional family who marries a progressive, modern woman.</p>\n\n<p>At the heart of the story is his mother an artist deeply rooted in cultural values, who strives to preserve the essence of tradition amidst change. As generations collide and perspectives shift, the family discovers a profound truth: a home is built not just by a couple, but by every individual bound together by understanding, respect, and love. Rich in humor and layered with heartfelt emotions, Kutumb Kirrtan is an engaging drama that beautifully celebrates the true spirit of family.</p>\n\n<p>Language of drama: Marathi</p>\n\n<style>\n.location-page-temp {display: block!important;}\n@media screen and (max-width: 600px){iframe{width:100%;}}\n</style>\n"
      }
    ],
