    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Paquette Productions Presents Legends Show - Tribute to Everly Brothers, Blues Brothers, Motown & Elvis"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>'Legends Show' brings you some of North America's most exciting performers live on stage. Accompanied by the 'Rockin' Royals Band', this show will feature the most incredible Tributes to the Everly Brothers, the Blues Brothers, the Music of Motown, and Elvis Presley. </p>\n\n<p>As <b>The Everly Brothers</b>: American rock duo, the Everly Brothers, were known for their steel string acoustic guitar playing and close harmony singing. Consisting of 'Don' Everly'  (performed by Pete Paquette) and Phil Everly (performed by Luke Wilson), the duo combined  elements of rock and roll, country, and pop, becoming pioneers of country rock.</p>\n\n<p>As <b>The Blues Brothers</b>, Chris and Geoff Dahl (real brothers from London, Ontario), shared the  stage with some of the world's top R&B legends including BB King, The Contours, The  Miracles, Martha Reeves, to name a few. Their full SOUL BROTHERS show has taken the  brothers all over the world performing the hits of legendary R&B recording artists The Blues  Brothers, The Isley Brothers, Sam and Dave, James Brown, Ray Charles and more...</p>\n\n<p>The <b>Music of Motown</b>: The stars of 'Motown Soul' take the stage, Cathy and Marlene known  as The Tonettes, have been blessed with power, sensitivity, and vocal energy. This sensational  duo will be performing a variety of songs from the music of Diana Ross and The Supremes,  Aretha Franklin and many others. A performance not to be missed. </p>\n\n<p>As <b>Elvis Presley</b>, Pete Paquette is a Multi-Award winning Elvis Tribute Artist. Known for  captivating his audiences through his incredible voice, high energy, charisma, and playful  spontaneity with his audiences, a performer that will leave you wanting more.</p>\n\n<style>\n@media screen and (max-width: 600px){iframe{width:100%;}}\n.location-page-temp {display: block!important;}\n</style>"
      }
    ],
