    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ww2.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=7621"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/url": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ww2.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=7621"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Rellik - Maclab Indigenous Series"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "\n<p>Bill LeBlanc, better known as <b>RELLIK</b> in the entertainment world, is an accomplished recording artist, performer, and radio host hailing from Edmonton. With a career spanning over two decades and decorated with 11 awards and 35 nominations, Rellik has solidified his presence in the industry.</p>\n\n<p>Renowned for his ability to blend genres and create distinctive musical landscapes, he also spent many years on Indigenous radio airwaves, having hosted the afterrnon Drive show on 89.3 The Raven for over four years and currently hosts the 'Coffee and Cree' podcast, as he is also a strong advocate in Cree language revitalization. </p>\n\n<p>In recent years, Rellik and his unique blend of Country, Rock and Hip Hop have entertained audiences at The Beaumont Music Festival, K Days, The International Fringe Festival Mainstage, Pembina River Nights, Edmonton Heritage Festival, Taste of Edmonton, Downtown Spark, Onoway Heritage Days and so many more.</p>\n\n<p>Beyond his musical endeavours and radio commitments, <b>RELLIK</b> actively contributes to his community, embodying a true family man and a man of traditional ceremony and values when he's not on stage or in the studio. Time spent with his wife and kids is a testament to his unwavering dedication to both his art and his loved ones.</p>\n\n\n<p><a href='https://www.facebook.com/Rellik118' target='_blank'>Rellik - Facebook</a></p>\n\n\n<style>\n.location-page-temp {\n    display: block!important;}\n@media screen and (max-width: 600px){iframe{width:100%;}}\n</style>"
      }
    ],
