    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Tartan Terrors: 30 Years Of Terror "
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>The Tartan Terrors are celebrating 30 years of bringing high-energy Celtic music to the world! With 11 CDs, numerous DVDs, and 1000's of live shows, this dynamic group have performed at such iconic venues as the Iridium on Broadway, Dublin Irish Festival, Loon Mountain New Hampshire and on Good Morning America. Having performed for Queen Elizabeth as well as President Clinton's inauguration, their award winning sound blends traditional Celtic music with rock 'n' roll. Over the years they have shared the stage with Eileen Ivers, Dropkick Murphys, and Ally The Piper to name a few. Featuring bagpipes, drums, fiddles, guitars, and dancing the Tartan Terrors have played over 48 U.S. states, 5 countries, and have entertained millions of fans worldwide. 'These guys are high energy and they leave everything on the stage' Hunters Bay Radio</p>\n\n\n<style>\n@media screen and (max-width: 600px){\niframe{width:100%;}\n}\n</style>"
      }
    ],
