        "@id": "https://ww2.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=7644"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "The Bright Side of Charley Pride Starring Ali Bright"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "\n<p>&ldquo;Ali Bright captures the essence of Charley Pride perfectly&rdquo;. &ndash; Warren Berg, CFWE Radio</p>\n\n<p>&ldquo;20 years of covering Charley, Ali Bright is the closest experience yet&rdquo; &ndash; Bill Borgwardt, Country Music News / Alberta Country Music Archives</p>\n\n<p>&ldquo;Amazing Show and Performance&rdquo; &ndash; Sean Smith, CFCW Radio</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p><b>ABOUT THE SHOW</b></p>\n\n<p>Welcome to an evening of timeless music and heartfelt tribute. We invite you to step into the life and legacy of the Bright Side Of Charley Pride. The voice and presence of Ali Bright honor the spirit and songs of Charley Pride in the Bright Side Of Charley Pride. Together they journey through decades of hits, heart warming stories and the break through moments that helped Charley become a pioneer in country music. 70 Million records sold worldwide, 39 No #1 Hits, 52 Billboard Top #10s and a multitude of awards including 3 Grammys.</p>\n \n<p>Join Ali Bright as he guides us through Prides life, starting in the cotton fields of Mississippi, continuing through his career pitching in the old Nigro Leagues and ultimately making records and breaking records in the music industry. Already playing to sold out houses in Western Canada, The Bright Side Of Charley Pride is a natural fit for theatres and Show rooms of all sizes. Experience the legend, the music and the incredible story of &ldquo;The Bright Side Of Charley Pride&rdquo;.</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p><b>ABOUT ALI BRIGHT</b></p>\n\n<p>Ali Bright grew up in a huge family of 16 children in the East Coast town of Danvers, Nova Scotia. At a tender age Ali cut his teeth performing in his family band and appearing at community events. As a young man Ali heard his calling, joining the Canadian military, spending 22 years serving his country as a military veteran. Bright won a string of talent contests in the 1990's including Nova Scotia's Bud Country Talent Search and the 103.9 FM Radio Star Search in Edmonton, AB. Ali Bright released his debut album &ldquo;Desparate Man&rdquo; in 1995 while touring Western Canada. Ali's gentle personality and rich soothing vocals, combined with the influence of Charley's music, make him the ideal artist to pay tribute to a great country legend.</p>\n\n\n<iframe width='560' height='315' src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/GNuY9b7iQis?si=ch2iIgTQZJzcylCx' title='YouTube video player' frameborder='0' allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share' referrerpolicy='strict-origin-when-cross-origin' allowfullscreen></iframe>\n\n<style>\n@media screen and (max-width: 600px){\niframe{width:100%;}\n}\n\n</style>\n\n```"
      }
