      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Tramp of the Century - The Breakfast in America Tour"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "\n<p><b>BREAKFAST IN AMERICA | TRAMP OF THE CENTURY</b></p>\n<p> In 1979, the album Breakfast In America was the most popular album on the planet, with more than 20 million copies sold. Sales in Canada are of course there, with nearly 1 million copies sold, including more than 400,000 in Quebec. In the same year, Supertramp organized a huge tour in Europe and North America. It was during this tour that the album 'Live in Paris' was recorded. It was the same year that Montreal welcomed the British band to Jarry Park for 2 grandiose shows, with Jean-Luc Ponty as the opening act, which still mark the imagination of fans who had the pleasure of attending. Tramp of the Century wants to allow its fans to relive this period when, both on record and on stage, the members of Supertramp are at their peak. Always striving to interpret this magnificent music with authenticity, passion and attention to detail, Tramp of the Century invites you to this show paying tribute to those nights under the stars, the Breakfast In America tours of 1979.</p>\n\n\n<style>\n@media screen and (max-width: 600px){\niframe{width:100%;}\n}\n</style>"
      }
    ],
